    h4.mt-4#notation Notation
    p.mt-2.mb-3 This tutorial uses a special notation for representing HTML structures. For example, consider a 
      a(href="components-2.html#button-group-button-toolbar") button toolbar
      |  as below.
    div.btn-toolbar(role="toolbar" aria-label="Button toolbar")
      div.btn-group(role="group" aria-label="Group 1")
        each text in ["1","2","3"]
          button.btn.btn-secondary(role="button")= text
      div.btn-group.ml-2(role="group" aria-label="Group 2")
        each text in ["A","B"]
          button.btn.btn-secondary(role="button")= text
    pre.mt-3.p-2.border.bg-light
      code
        = `<div class="btn-toolbar" role="toolbar" aria-label="Button toolbar">\n`
        = `  <div class="btn-group" role="group" aria-label="Group 1">\n`
        = `    <button class="btn btn-secondary" role="button">1</button>\n`
        = `    <button class="btn btn-secondary" role="button">2</button>\n`
        = `    <button class="btn btn-secondary" role="button">3</button>\n`
        = `  </div>\n`
        = `  <div class="btn-group ml-2" role="group" aria-label="Group 2">\n`
        = `    <button class="btn btn-secondary" role="button">A</button>\n`
        = `    <button class="btn btn-secondary" role="button">B</button>\n`
        = `  </div>\n`
        = `</div>`
    p.my-2 The tutorial describes it with annotated nested list as follows.
    ul
      li Pressing 
        button.btn.btn-outline-info Structure
        |  button shows whole structure with nested list
        ul
          li Pressing 
            button.btn.btn-sm.btn-outline-info.my-1.px-1.py-0 Attributes
            |  button shows attributes for each element
    +collapseButton("#example-structure") Structure
    |  ‚áê Click!
    ul.struct.collapse.my-3#example-structure
      li Button toolbar
        code div.btn-toolbar
        +attrsBtn(".a1-1")
        ul
          li.att.collapse.a1-1 Accessibility attribute 
            code role="toolbar"
          li.att.collapse.a1-1 Accessibility attribute 
            code aria-label="Button toolbar"
          li (First) button group 
            code div.btn-group
            +attrsBtn(".a1-2")
            ul
              li.att.collapse.a1-2 Accessibility attribute 
                code role="group"
              li.att.collapse.a1-2 Accessibility attribute 
                code aria-label="Group 1"
              li Button 
                code button.btn
                |  (&times;3)
                +attrsBtn(".a1-3")
                ul
                  li.cls.collapse.a1-3 Button color 
                    code .btn-secondary
                  li.att.collapse.a1-3 Accessibility attribute 
                    code role="button"
                  li.txt Text 
                    code 1
                    | , 
                    code 2
                    | , 
                    code 3
          li (Second) button group 
            code div.btn-group
            +attrsBtn(".a1-4")
            ul
              li.cls.collapse.a1-4 Left margin 
                code .ml-2
              li.att.collapse.a1-4 Accessibility attribute 
                code role="group"
              li.att.collapse.a1-4 Accessibility attribute 
                code aria-label="Group 2"
              li Button 
                code button.btn
                |  (&times;2)
                +attrsBtn(".a1-5")
                ul
                  li.cls.collapse.a1-5 Button color 
                    code .btn-secondary
                  li.att.collapse.a1-5 Accessibility attribute 
                    code role="button"
                  li.txt Text 
                    code A
                    | , 
                    code B
    p.my-2 Notation rules are as follows.
    ul.struct
      li Element: black prefix marker (
        code disc
        | ), element name with 
        code code
        |  (red monospace text)
      li Element with class(es): CSS dot notation: e.g. 
        code div.modal.fade
      li Attributes, (additional) classes, and child elements are described with nested lists
        ul
          li.cls Additional class(es): white prefix marker (
            code circle
            | ), CSS dot notation: 
            code .{class1}.{class2}
          li.att Attribute: white prefix marker (
            code circle
            | ), HTML attribute notation: 
            code {attribute}="{value}"
          li.txt Text: no prifix marker (
            code none
            | ), e.g. 
            code Text content
          li Descendant elements use same notation as parents, also use nesting to describe hierarchy

